title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\InsertResponse
name: InsertResponse
description:
Represents the result of streaming data into a table.

This class should be not instantiated directly, but as a result of calling Google\Cloud\BigQuery\Table::insertRow() or Google\Cloud\BigQuery\Table::insertRows().

params.name: rows
params.description: The rows provided in the original request.

methods.name: failedRows
methods.description: Returns the rows which failed to insert along with their associated errors and index in the original data set.
